{
  "texts": [
    "It is also interesting to see why similar dynamics do not transpire under complete networks.",
    "In this case, all agents will see both articles, which have the same reliability but argue for opposite perspectives.",
    "In consequence, their overall effects will cancel each other and the posterior belief distribution H will continue to coincide with the prior distribution H, exhibiting no voter polarization.",
    "In more general settings, left-leaning and right-leaning articles may have different credibilities, and it is natural to assume that the right-leaning articles will have greater credibility when θ = R and vice versa.",
    "If so, then with a complete network, people will update their priors and posterior distribution will shift in the direction of the truth."
  ]
}